WEBVTT

00:00.500 --> 00:03.993
Man: The exhibit was
a paradox of absurdity,

00:04.000 --> 00:05.559
Impressionistic
and surreal.

00:05.570 --> 00:09.438
The choice of sunlight to create
such darkness was stunning.

00:09.440 --> 00:12.239
Oh, it's exciting to
have such a talent

00:12.240 --> 00:14.777
Emerge from
the |.A. Art scene.

00:14.780 --> 00:16.475
I was moved
by the boldness.

00:16.480 --> 00:17.879
Man: It was
absolutely sublime.

00:17.880 --> 00:20.975
Woman: We'll raise lots
of money on this, andrea.

00:20.980 --> 00:22.516
Well done. Ha ha ha!

00:22.520 --> 00:24.215
Man: A toast to our
enchanting hostess

00:24.220 --> 00:27.315
And committee chair
andrea brown.

00:27.320 --> 00:28.583
You've outdone
yourself, my dear.

00:28.590 --> 00:30.558
Thank you, walt,
but I couldn't do it

00:30.560 --> 00:32.722
Without my illustrious
board members,

00:32.729 --> 00:35.028
And tonight is
about my gratitude

00:35.030 --> 00:38.261
For your tireless
fundraising efforts.

00:38.270 --> 00:38.930
Thank you.

00:38.930 --> 00:40.523
Cheers.
Cheers. Well done.

00:40.540 --> 00:42.429
Congratulations.
Thank you.

00:42.440 --> 00:45.034
Yeah.
Mm. Mm.

00:45.040 --> 00:47.259
Did you pay
your bills, andrea?

00:47.280 --> 00:49.908
[laughter]

00:49.910 --> 00:53.073
Robyn, can you check
the fuse box, sweetie?

00:53.080 --> 00:54.343
Think we have
a short.

00:54.350 --> 00:55.749
Of course.

00:55.750 --> 01:00.039
Oh, well, maybe not.
Ha ha ha! Never mind.

01:00.060 --> 01:03.212
Mood lighting.
Sorry about that.

01:03.230 --> 01:04.959
Mm.
Ok.

01:04.959 --> 01:07.383
[dog barking]

01:07.400 --> 01:09.255
And that
would be roxy.

01:09.270 --> 01:13.969
Excuse me. I'm so sorry.
This is embarrassing.

01:13.970 --> 01:16.029
Make sure
she's ok.

01:16.040 --> 01:17.462
Excuse me.

01:17.470 --> 01:20.064
[barking continues]

01:20.080 --> 01:23.004
Roxy? Come here, girl.
What is it?

01:23.010 --> 01:24.000
[barking]

01:24.010 --> 01:26.399
What's the matter,
sweetie?

01:28.720 --> 01:29.846
[feedback]

01:29.850 --> 01:34.310
[music playing]

01:40.060 --> 01:41.994
What is that?

01:42.000 --> 01:45.425
It's roberta flack.

01:45.430 --> 01:47.728
Oht

01:51.110 --> 01:56.901
It's him.
He was in my house.

02:25.610 --> 02:29.069
All right.

02:29.810 --> 02:32.074
Hey, you got
your homework?

02:32.080 --> 02:33.104
Ethan: Yes.

02:33.120 --> 02:35.077
Books?
Yes.

02:35.080 --> 02:38.345
Oh, I forgot
my lunch.

02:38.350 --> 02:42.719
Get in the car.
I'll get it.

02:48.160 --> 02:52.028
Ethan: Hey.
It's you again.

02:52.030 --> 02:54.897
Just morning run.

02:54.900 --> 02:57.039
You live around here?

02:57.040 --> 02:58.769
Yeah.

02:58.770 --> 03:03.332
I'm ethan.

03:04.480 --> 03:05.504
Wesley.

03:05.510 --> 03:07.649
Nice to meet you,
wesley.

03:07.650 --> 03:09.539
Those boys
from Halloween

03:09.550 --> 03:10.847
Still giving you
trouble?

03:10.850 --> 03:13.615
Nah. You pretty much
fixed them.

03:13.620 --> 03:16.749
Good.
Headed to school?

03:16.760 --> 03:19.058
Yeah.

03:19.060 --> 03:21.324
Where's your mom?

03:21.330 --> 03:22.752
She had court
this morning,

03:22.770 --> 03:25.899
So her boyfriend
trent is taking me.

03:25.900 --> 03:27.994
You don't like him?

03:28.000 --> 03:29.638
He's ok, I guess.

03:29.640 --> 03:32.462
Trent: Ethan, let's go.

03:32.470 --> 03:36.236
Ok. Coming.
I got to...Go.

03:40.950 --> 03:43.271
You don't talk
to strangers.

03:43.290 --> 03:47.818
- He's not.
He lives around here.

04:01.840 --> 04:03.569
Morning.

04:03.570 --> 04:05.732
Morning.
Nice house.

04:05.740 --> 04:07.560
Very. Belongs
to andrea brown.

04:07.580 --> 04:09.435
She filed a report
with us two weeks ago.

04:09.450 --> 04:11.270
We obtained
a restraining order

04:11.280 --> 04:12.645
And against her ex-husband,
and he was being

04:12.650 --> 04:14.140
A good boy
until last night.

04:14.150 --> 04:16.414
I read the police report--
breaking and entering,

04:16.420 --> 04:19.617
Vandalism.

04:20.920 --> 04:23.855
Jack: Is this what
you call I.A. Art?

04:23.860 --> 04:25.680
Mm. You're funny.

04:25.690 --> 04:26.919
Andrea brown
runs the board

04:26.930 --> 04:28.659
For the doheny museum
art project.

04:28.660 --> 04:31.129
It's a fancy nonprofit
that raises money

04:31.130 --> 04:33.895
For various charities
by auctioning off

04:33.900 --> 04:37.268
The work of new
and important artists.

04:37.270 --> 04:38.760
Is that
a real job?

04:38.770 --> 04:39.601
Philanthropy.

04:39.610 --> 04:40.839
Andrea is
independently wealthy

04:40.840 --> 04:42.433
Due to a fat
divorce settlement.

04:42.440 --> 04:43.930
So an angry ex
is behind this.

04:43.950 --> 04:47.409
Yes--kenneth brown.
He's a real estate developer.

04:47.420 --> 04:49.218
He made a fortune
in the nineties,

04:49.220 --> 04:50.472
Happy couple until--

04:50.490 --> 04:51.810
He cheated on her,
and she took him

04:51.820 --> 04:52.742
For everything
he had.

04:52.760 --> 04:54.512
She got it all,
including the dog.

04:54.520 --> 04:56.249
All he got was
a bad real estate market,

04:56.260 --> 04:58.729
Debt, and the fake blond
with the fake tan

04:58.730 --> 04:59.879
And the fake boobies.

04:59.900 --> 05:01.129
Seriously,
that sounds like

05:01.130 --> 05:03.349
Some horrible
|.A. Cliche.

05:03.370 --> 05:04.622
We love cliches.

05:04.630 --> 05:06.769
We live them,
make movies about them.

05:06.770 --> 05:08.295
It's the |.A.
Way of life.

05:08.300 --> 05:10.189
You'll get
the hang of it.

05:10.210 --> 05:11.905
You called them
boobies?

05:11.910 --> 05:17.132
It's daytime, jack.
I try to keep it g-rated.

05:18.850 --> 05:21.273
Andrea: I knew kenneth
was an angry bastard,

05:21.280 --> 05:23.510
But this was
one step too far.

05:23.520 --> 05:24.510
Can you relay
the events

05:24.520 --> 05:26.113
That led to
the restraining order?

05:26.120 --> 05:29.181
Ask detective lawrence.
She knows all of this.

05:29.190 --> 05:30.260
She's handling my case.

05:30.260 --> 05:31.819
I understand,
but sometimes new details

05:31.830 --> 05:34.822
Can surface
from our memory.

05:34.830 --> 05:37.925
It started with
harassing phone calls,

05:37.930 --> 05:39.523
And then he accosted me

05:39.540 --> 05:41.099
In a restaurant
one night.

05:41.100 --> 05:43.364
He wanted to borrow
money, and I said no,

05:43.370 --> 05:44.804
And he tried
to strangle me.

05:44.810 --> 05:46.539
They had to
pry him off me.

05:46.540 --> 05:49.134
Is that when
you called tau?

05:49.140 --> 05:52.974
Tell me about
your marriage.

05:52.980 --> 05:55.369
Kenneth and I were
married for 15 years.

05:55.380 --> 05:58.441
It was a good marriage,
wasn't perfect,

05:58.450 --> 06:01.784
But it worked
for a long time.

06:01.790 --> 06:03.189
We loved each other.

06:03.190 --> 06:05.522
Why'd you
get divorced?

06:05.530 --> 06:07.589
People grow apart.

06:07.600 --> 06:10.752
His eyes started to
wander to younger women.

06:10.770 --> 06:13.819
He cheated, and once
the trust is gone,

06:13.840 --> 06:15.069
So is the marriage.

06:15.070 --> 06:18.563
I understand kenneth
is very unhappy.

06:18.570 --> 06:21.437
I got what we agreed to
in the prenup,

06:21.440 --> 06:23.579
And now he wants
to ruin me

06:23.580 --> 06:26.402
With my work,
my friends.

06:26.420 --> 06:28.149
He's making
a mockery of me.

06:28.150 --> 06:30.278
Jack: Mrs. Brown,
what's the significance

06:30.290 --> 06:32.816
Of the song
that was playing?

06:32.820 --> 06:35.755
It was the song we danced
to on our first date.

06:35.760 --> 06:37.080
It's been our song
ever since.

06:37.090 --> 06:39.388
Do you think that there's
a part of your ex-husband

06:39.400 --> 06:40.356
That still loves you?

06:40.360 --> 06:42.590
- No. Our love
is dead, detective.

06:42.600 --> 06:45.160
He hates me now,
and that's just fine.

06:45.170 --> 06:48.265
Just want him
to leave me alone.

06:48.270 --> 06:49.362
We'll talk to him.

06:49.370 --> 06:51.930
I filed the report and
got a restraining order.

06:51.940 --> 06:53.635
Can't you just
arrest him?

06:53.640 --> 06:55.039
Beth: We know this
is scary for you.

06:55.040 --> 06:57.429
No. Actually,
I'm frustrated,

06:57.450 --> 07:00.499
And, yes, I'm scared
because I know kenneth,

07:00.520 --> 07:04.070
And he has a temper,
and he resents me.

07:04.090 --> 07:06.843
He's not gonna stop.

07:10.860 --> 07:13.488
Robyn: I've worked for andrea
for several months now.

07:13.500 --> 07:15.696
Do you know
her ex-husband?

07:15.700 --> 07:16.553
Not very well,

07:16.570 --> 07:19.267
But I do know
he has a temper.

07:19.270 --> 07:21.898
And how is your
relationship with andrea?

07:21.900 --> 07:24.369
Very good.
I respect her.

07:24.370 --> 07:26.737
She's a very
strong woman,

07:26.740 --> 07:28.606
And when you're
a strong woman,

07:28.610 --> 07:30.203
People call you
callous,

07:30.210 --> 07:31.541
Heartless bitch,
but I saw

07:31.550 --> 07:33.439
What the divorce
did to her.

07:33.450 --> 07:35.077
It broke her heart.

07:35.080 --> 07:37.174
Thank you for speaking
with me, robyn.

07:37.190 --> 07:38.680
Yeah. No problem.

07:38.690 --> 07:39.839
Jack: Looks like you
control the lights

07:39.860 --> 07:41.453
By the panel located
in the garage,

07:41.460 --> 07:42.950
No prints, but
the security system

07:42.960 --> 07:44.280
Has 4 digital cameras.

07:44.290 --> 07:45.360
I'm getting
the drive.

07:45.360 --> 07:46.919
Get that footage to ben.
He's fast with it.

07:46.930 --> 07:48.921
See if you can get
kenneth's face on camera.

07:48.930 --> 07:53.492
Janice, come with me.
You know the ex already.

07:53.500 --> 07:56.697
Kenneth: Well,
I didn't do it.

07:56.710 --> 07:58.337
I was home all night.

07:58.340 --> 07:59.830
He was home
all night.

07:59.840 --> 08:00.739
You were with him?

08:00.740 --> 08:04.108
No. I had my pilates
class last night.

08:04.110 --> 08:05.999
Then how do you
know he was home?

08:06.010 --> 08:08.513
Because
he said so.

08:08.520 --> 08:09.874
Kenneth: I'm not lying.

08:09.890 --> 08:11.881
The woman filed
a restraining order against me.

08:11.890 --> 08:14.143
I'm not going within
10 miles of that bitch.

08:14.160 --> 08:15.559
Yeah.
She's crazy.

08:15.560 --> 08:17.289
You attacked her
in a restaurant.

08:17.290 --> 08:20.157
Kenneth: I was angry.
She took all my money.

08:20.160 --> 08:22.458
I have a mortgage
that I can't pay.

08:22.460 --> 08:23.393
Yes. I lost
my temper.

08:23.400 --> 08:25.459
Beth: Like you're
doing right now?

08:25.470 --> 08:26.995
Maybe you need
to calm down.

08:27.000 --> 08:30.630
It's ok, honey.
She's testing you.

08:30.640 --> 08:32.301
She's trying
to make you mad.

08:32.309 --> 08:34.107
I know
this tactic.

08:34.110 --> 08:35.032
How so?

08:35.039 --> 08:37.475
You're doing it
to me now.

08:37.480 --> 08:40.972
Listen. We have done
nothing but suffer

08:40.980 --> 08:44.041
At the hands of this
crazy woman.

08:44.049 --> 08:45.347
She took
everything.

08:45.350 --> 08:47.717
What did she take
of yours, melissa?

08:47.720 --> 08:49.381
One could argue
that you are

08:49.390 --> 08:51.688
The one who did
the taking.

08:51.690 --> 08:53.283
Do we need
to call a lawyer?

08:53.300 --> 08:54.688
Do you need
to call a lawyer?

08:54.700 --> 08:55.656
Stop doing that.

08:55.660 --> 08:56.889
Melissa, sweetie,
it's ok.

08:56.900 --> 08:58.698
No. It's not.
I'm tired of her.

08:58.700 --> 09:00.122
Why doesn't she just
leave us alone?

09:00.140 --> 09:01.835
She is the one
that's harassing us.

09:01.840 --> 09:06.232
Listen. Andrea went off
the deep end after the divorce.

09:06.240 --> 09:08.572
You sure it wasn't
after your affair?

09:08.580 --> 09:10.275
I know that what I did
doesn't make me sound

09:10.280 --> 09:11.748
Like the most
upstanding guy,

09:11.750 --> 09:13.775
But I am not
stalking andrea,

09:13.780 --> 09:15.748
And I certainly didn't
break into her house.

09:15.750 --> 09:17.639
I have better things
to do with my time,

09:17.650 --> 09:20.119
Like digging myself
out of this gutter hole

09:20.120 --> 09:21.758
That she put me in.

09:21.760 --> 09:23.512
He's telling
the truth.

09:23.530 --> 09:25.282
Do you know of anyone
else in her life

09:25.290 --> 09:26.780
Who might
want to hurt her?

09:26.800 --> 09:28.495
Anyone who
knows the bitch.

09:28.500 --> 09:31.128
I'm telling you,
andrea is a mean woman.

09:31.130 --> 09:32.894
Look. I know that I hurt her,
but she was

09:32.900 --> 09:35.995
Just as cruel and
vindictive in the divorce.

09:36.000 --> 09:38.094
She ruined me.

09:38.110 --> 09:40.704
And roberta flack?

09:40.710 --> 09:44.908
Huh? Who's that?

09:44.910 --> 09:48.471
She's a singer.

09:48.480 --> 09:50.244
I've never
heard of her.

09:50.250 --> 09:52.014
"First time ever
I saw your face"

09:52.020 --> 09:54.614
Is the song
in question.

09:54.620 --> 09:59.023
She told you
about that song.

09:59.030 --> 10:00.225
What song?

10:00.230 --> 10:03.291
It was mine and andrea's
song as a couple.

10:03.300 --> 10:06.668
Well, what's our song?
We don't have a song.

10:06.670 --> 10:08.968
All right.
We'll get a song.

10:08.970 --> 10:13.009
Look. I'm not
stalking my ex-wife, ok?

10:13.010 --> 10:16.503
I want her gone
from my life.

10:16.510 --> 10:19.150
You understand?

10:19.150 --> 10:20.675
Ben: I've got a man
wearing a ski mask.

10:20.680 --> 10:22.148
He clearly knew
where the cameras were.

10:22.150 --> 10:23.845
You see how he's walking
backwards in certain areas?

10:23.850 --> 10:25.887
Janice: The man's build
could easily be kenneth.

10:25.890 --> 10:27.585
It's not enough.
We need a face.

10:27.590 --> 10:29.217
What do we know about
the divorce settlement?

10:29.220 --> 10:31.257
Well, kenneth and andrea
married in '98.

10:31.260 --> 10:33.058
He accrued a net worth
of $27 million

10:33.060 --> 10:35.051
In the first decade
of their marriage.

10:35.060 --> 10:37.256
Beth: California
is a no-fault state.

10:37.270 --> 10:39.466
How did andrea
end up with so much?

10:39.470 --> 10:42.337
If kenneth cheated, andrea
got 90% of everything.

10:42.340 --> 10:43.739
According to court
transcripts,

10:43.740 --> 10:45.265
Kenneth's lawyers
argued that andrea

10:45.270 --> 10:46.567
Was psychologically
unbalanced,

10:46.580 --> 10:48.400
That her deranged behavior
was as much of a cause

10:48.410 --> 10:50.401
For the failed marriage
as kenneth's infidelity.

10:50.410 --> 10:52.504
There was no proof of it,
and a judge sympathized

10:52.510 --> 10:56.219
And awarded her 95% of
their net worth for defamation.

10:56.220 --> 10:57.449
California
is tough.

10:57.450 --> 10:59.509
Beth: Seems like
revenge stalking.

10:59.520 --> 11:01.147
Serves a
psychological need,

11:01.160 --> 11:02.082
A way of holding on

11:02.090 --> 11:03.251
To the person
being stalked.

11:03.260 --> 11:04.557
Janice: So kenneth
is trying to maintain

11:04.560 --> 11:06.028
A connection with andrea,
even while he goes about

11:06.030 --> 11:07.520
Destroying everything
in her life

11:07.530 --> 11:09.020
That she took
away from him?

11:09.030 --> 11:10.100
Why would he do that?

11:10.100 --> 11:13.161
It could explain the
song, a nostalgic ploy.

11:13.170 --> 11:14.160
It's so cliched.

11:14.170 --> 11:17.037
I told you.
We love our cliches here.

11:17.040 --> 11:18.599
They even come
with a soundtrack.

11:18.610 --> 11:19.634
But roberta flack?

11:19.640 --> 11:21.039
What are you
talking about?

11:21.040 --> 11:22.576
Your life has
a soundtrack, ben.

11:22.580 --> 11:23.809
No, it doesn't.

11:23.810 --> 11:25.904
What were you listening to
on the way to work?

11:25.910 --> 11:27.400
"The carpenters'
greatest hits."

11:27.420 --> 11:29.013
You should keep that
to yourself.

11:29.020 --> 11:31.079
Ben: And
you're so cool?

11:31.090 --> 11:31.909
Pearl jam.

11:31.920 --> 11:33.740
"White-winged dove,"
stevie nicks.

11:33.760 --> 11:36.183
Everyone
IS so retro.

11:36.190 --> 11:38.625
And you?
What?

11:38.630 --> 11:40.985
Song?
Let's focus on kenneth.

11:41.000 --> 11:42.525
Traffic cams,
parking tickets.

11:42.530 --> 11:44.123
Let's see if he
was in the vicinity

11:44.130 --> 11:45.996
Of andrea's house
violating

11:46.000 --> 11:47.525
That restraining
order,

11:47.540 --> 11:52.660
And, jack, it's
a pat benatar day.

11:55.280 --> 11:57.430
Andrea: They'll have to
walk through the exhibit

11:57.450 --> 11:58.702
To get to the bar
to get drunk,

11:58.710 --> 12:02.214
Which is what they're
coming for, anyway...

12:02.220 --> 12:03.517
Perfect.

12:03.520 --> 12:07.684
And I want flowers
on all the tables.

12:08.960 --> 12:10.485
What's that?

12:10.490 --> 12:11.480
Oh, it's for you.

12:11.490 --> 12:13.458
It was delivered
before I got here.

12:13.460 --> 12:16.896
Were you expecting
a package?

12:16.900 --> 12:19.562
Read the card.

12:19.570 --> 12:22.392
Mm...

12:22.400 --> 12:23.834
"do not be greedy.

12:23.840 --> 12:24.762
"Because
of these sins,

12:24.770 --> 12:29.731
The wrath of god
is coming upon you."

12:31.150 --> 12:33.448
No!

12:33.450 --> 12:36.545
Oh, my god, no.

12:36.550 --> 12:40.942
Please. No, no, no.

12:46.790 --> 12:50.954
I don't understand how
anyone could do this.

12:50.970 --> 12:54.395
It's so cruel.

12:54.400 --> 12:55.765
You said that you
and kenneth

12:55.770 --> 12:57.795
Got the dog when
you were married?

12:57.810 --> 13:00.199
Yes, 10 years ago.

13:00.210 --> 13:02.770
He loved roxy
as much as I did.

13:02.780 --> 13:04.771
I mean, even
after the divorce,

13:04.780 --> 13:09.149
Kenneth used to keep
her on the weekends,

13:09.150 --> 13:12.017
I mean, at least
until melissa moved in.

13:12.020 --> 13:13.215
Then what happened?

13:13.220 --> 13:16.588
Oh, she didn't
like the dog.

13:16.590 --> 13:19.252
She wouldn't let
roxy come over anymore.

13:19.260 --> 13:22.457
Janice: The message sent
to andrea is from the bible--

13:22.460 --> 13:24.895
Colossians chapter 3,
verses 5 and 6.

13:24.900 --> 13:26.664
"Do not be greedy,
for a greedy person

13:26.670 --> 13:28.695
"is an idolater worshipping
the things of the world.

13:28.700 --> 13:32.659
Because of these sins, the wrath
of god is coming upon you."

13:32.670 --> 13:34.764
Ben: And we looked
into melissa barnes.

13:34.780 --> 13:35.975
Her father
was a pastor.

13:35.980 --> 13:38.130
