I want you to know
when I first met kenneth

29:54.660 --> 29:58.619
I didn't know that
he was married,

29:58.630 --> 30:03.750
And, andrea, I never
meant to hurt you.

30:03.760 --> 30:05.797
I'm sorry.

30:05.800 --> 30:07.461
I've been waiting
such a long time

30:07.470 --> 30:10.189
To hear you
say that.

30:10.200 --> 30:13.261
Come in, please.

30:13.540 --> 30:17.033
Maybe now we can
both start to heal.

30:17.040 --> 30:18.735
Hyah!

30:39.530 --> 30:43.034
Finally, you're awake.

30:44.670 --> 30:48.038
This isn't gonna work
if you're passed out.

30:48.040 --> 30:50.407
Andrea, please.

30:50.410 --> 30:53.710
Please let me go, ok?

30:53.710 --> 30:54.506
I'm sorry.

30:54.520 --> 30:57.410
"Oh, I'm sorry.
Let me go.

30:57.420 --> 30:58.649
I'm sorry!"

30:58.650 --> 31:01.085
An apology doesn't
mean anything!

31:01.090 --> 31:04.355
You took him
from me!

31:04.360 --> 31:05.919
When kenneth first
started out,

31:05.930 --> 31:06.829
I was there for him.

31:06.830 --> 31:09.026
I made him everything
that he was,

31:09.030 --> 31:10.259
And I can do that
again,

31:10.260 --> 31:11.819
He's gonna get out
of jail one day,

31:11.830 --> 31:13.127
And I'm gonna be
here for him,

31:13.130 --> 31:17.135
And you aren't gonna be
around to get in our way.

31:17.140 --> 31:20.906
Andrea, I left him.
Look. I promise.

31:20.910 --> 31:23.777
Please. Please just
let me go.

31:23.780 --> 31:26.101
Let you go?

31:27.150 --> 31:30.916
What, after you snuck
into my home,

31:30.920 --> 31:34.447
Hid here, waiting
to kill me?

31:34.460 --> 31:37.213
You are a very sick
young lady,

31:37.220 --> 31:38.881
And everyone knows that
you're the one

31:38.890 --> 31:40.380
With psychiatric
problems.

31:40.390 --> 31:44.793
You attacked me just like
you did your ex-boyfriend,

31:44.800 --> 31:45.949
And I had to
defend myself.

31:45.970 --> 31:48.166
I had no choice
but to kill you.

31:48.170 --> 31:53.040
I mean, after all, you and
kenneth have been stalking me.

31:53.040 --> 31:55.930
No--no one's gonna
believe that.

31:55.940 --> 31:57.010
Yes, they will.

31:57.010 --> 32:00.708
I have been working
on this plan for a long time.

32:00.710 --> 32:04.112
I have had nothing
to do but plan this,

32:04.120 --> 32:07.511
And it's going
surprisingly well.

32:07.520 --> 32:08.442
But...

32:08.460 --> 32:09.985
Ha ha ha!

32:09.990 --> 32:12.186
Melissa...

32:12.190 --> 32:13.726
There's nothing worse

32:13.730 --> 32:16.028
Than a divorced woman
with too much time

32:16.030 --> 32:19.295
And money
on her hands.

32:19.300 --> 32:21.723
Please. Andrea,
you can't--

32:21.740 --> 32:23.060
You can't do this.

32:23.070 --> 32:25.994
Please. I killed
my own dog.

32:26.010 --> 32:27.409
I can Kill you,

32:27.410 --> 32:29.879
And I actually--

32:29.880 --> 32:32.679
I liked roxy.

32:32.680 --> 32:35.479
You attacked me.

32:35.480 --> 32:38.518
Don't you remember
that, melissa?

32:38.520 --> 32:40.511
With this.

32:44.060 --> 32:47.428
And we fought!

32:49.830 --> 32:52.492
Aah! Aah!

32:59.970 --> 33:02.769
It's melissa's car.

33:05.450 --> 33:08.044
Let's go around back.

33:14.250 --> 33:17.254
[whimpering]

33:17.260 --> 33:19.615
I'm gonna untie
you now,

33:19.630 --> 33:22.190
And then you're
gonna stand up

33:22.200 --> 33:23.292
And walk towards me.

33:23.300 --> 33:25.758
Please. Please
don't do this.

33:25.770 --> 33:28.091
It'll all be over
in @ moment.

33:28.100 --> 33:31.035
[rattling]

33:57.560 --> 33:59.961
[muffled whimper]

34:04.840 --> 34:08.264
[muffled whimpering]

34:23.760 --> 34:24.909
Put the gun down.

34:24.929 --> 34:27.126
You got
what you wanted.

34:27.130 --> 34:30.690
Kenneth's in jail.

34:30.699 --> 34:32.520
I'll kill her.

34:32.530 --> 34:34.089
You don't want
to do that.

34:34.100 --> 34:35.989
Yes, I do.

34:36.000 --> 34:38.935
Doesn't anyone care
about what he did to me?

34:38.940 --> 34:40.135
I know. He cheated.

34:40.139 --> 34:43.678
He's a man.
That's what men do.

34:43.679 --> 34:45.569
Is that what you do?

34:45.580 --> 34:48.880
Have you cheated?

34:48.880 --> 34:51.610
Yes.

34:51.620 --> 34:53.940
Why?

34:56.719 --> 34:59.087
Yes. Why, jack?

35:03.430 --> 35:05.728
Why do men do that?

35:06.930 --> 35:09.024
Because I'm weak.

35:09.040 --> 35:11.759
I make
bad decisions.

35:11.770 --> 35:15.866
I ruin everything
worthwhile.

35:15.880 --> 35:17.632
I'm broken,

35:17.640 --> 35:19.039
And I can't
be fixed.

35:19.050 --> 35:21.007
No. Everyone can
be fixed.

35:21.010 --> 35:25.618
Kenneth is gonna be
fixed once she's gone.

35:25.620 --> 35:27.281
[gunshot]

35:27.290 --> 35:29.110
Aah!

35:52.880 --> 35:55.474
[sobbing]

35:58.890 --> 36:02.246
[music playing]

36:06.860 --> 36:08.988
Janice: Beth.

36:10.200 --> 36:11.622
Do you have a moment?

36:11.630 --> 36:13.325
Not if it involves
words like

36:13.330 --> 36:15.799
"I'm sorry,
why didn't I see it?"

36:15.800 --> 36:17.199
Or any other such
blame game lingo

36:17.200 --> 36:21.569
About how you didn't know
andrea brown was behind all this.

36:23.680 --> 36:26.240
I guess I don't
need a moment.

36:26.250 --> 36:29.675
Janice, go home,
open some wine,

36:29.680 --> 36:32.775
Listen to stevie nicks.

36:32.790 --> 36:35.043
We had a great day.

36:36.820 --> 36:42.054
Thank you, beth.
Good night.

36:42.060 --> 36:43.949
Good night.

36:55.840 --> 36:56.910
It's pearl jam.

36:56.910 --> 36:58.173
Nothing against
the carpenters,

36:58.180 --> 37:01.639
But it might be time to
step into a new decade.

37:01.650 --> 37:03.516
Cool.

37:12.460 --> 37:15.350
Jack: You work
long hours.

37:16.730 --> 37:18.459
I like what I do.

37:18.470 --> 37:23.237
Do you even have
a personal life?

37:23.240 --> 37:26.938
What do you want,
jack?

37:26.940 --> 37:29.329
I have a problem.

37:29.340 --> 37:33.004
It involves deputy d.A.
Amanda taylor.

37:46.360 --> 37:48.727
What about her?

37:48.730 --> 37:53.930
We had a relationship
back in new york.

37:53.930 --> 37:58.663
She got pregnant,
had a kid.

37:58.670 --> 38:00.809
I denied it was mine
for years.

38:00.810 --> 38:04.201
Back then, I wasn't
much of a father.

38:04.210 --> 38:08.943
I wasn't around,
I was-- I was horrible.

38:08.950 --> 38:11.214
Amanda and I had
a complicated relationship--

38:11.220 --> 38:13.712
Up and down, in and
out of each other's lives,

38:13.720 --> 38:18.783
<i>And she transferred
to .A. To get away from me,</i>

38:18.790 --> 38:23.023
But here I am.

38:23.030 --> 38:25.658
Is that it?

38:25.670 --> 38:30.767
No. I made other mistakes
while I was in new york,

38:30.770 --> 38:33.740
Things in my past
that could still hurt me,

38:33.740 --> 38:37.904
Jeopardize my career.

38:37.910 --> 38:39.708
Fix it.

38:41.710 --> 38:44.680
I don't know if it
can be fixed.

38:44.690 --> 38:47.682
I wouldn't know
where to begin.

38:47.690 --> 38:51.354
Well, the truth seems
to be working for you.

38:51.360 --> 38:53.010
Today anyway.

38:53.030 --> 38:57.854
Fix it, jack.
I'd hate to lose you.

39:01.200 --> 39:02.998
You're good.

39:03.000 --> 39:06.368
[music playing]

39:29.560 --> 39:30.630
Here we go again.

39:30.630 --> 39:31.756
Just a minute,
please.

39:31.770 --> 39:33.966
There's nothing more
to talk to you about, jack.

39:33.970 --> 39:35.790
I've got a meeting
with beth in the morning.

39:35.800 --> 39:37.689
Amanda, I--

39:37.700 --> 39:40.408
My father died.

39:42.610 --> 39:44.203
3 months ago.

39:44.210 --> 39:46.076
I didn't know.

39:46.080 --> 39:49.448
He wasn't such
a good guy.

39:49.450 --> 39:51.316
You knew that.

39:53.120 --> 39:55.612
And neither am I.

39:55.620 --> 39:59.318
I am sorry
for your loss,

39:59.330 --> 40:01.822
But whatever your grief
is coughing up right now

40:01.830 --> 40:02.922
Doesn't concern me.

40:02.930 --> 40:04.159
I get it.
You blame your father

40:04.160 --> 40:06.254
For all of your bad
behavior, and you should.

40:06.270 --> 40:11.265
He didn't give you one too
to cope with in this world,

40:11.270 --> 40:13.136
But I don't blame
your father.

40:13.140 --> 40:14.301
I only blame you.

40:14.310 --> 40:16.870
I know I hurt you,
and I can't undo it,

40:16.880 --> 40:18.439
But this is it, amanda.

40:18.450 --> 40:19.906
I'm begging you.

40:19.910 --> 40:22.345
I can change my life.

40:22.350 --> 40:25.547
I promise you I'll
stay away from ethan.

40:25.550 --> 40:26.847
Please just let me stay.

40:26.850 --> 40:28.545
I can make it here,
I can make it work.

40:28.560 --> 40:30.255
I know I can.
I can prove it.

40:30.260 --> 40:32.718
Maybe--maybe not
today or tomorrow,

40:32.730 --> 40:34.880
But one day, you'll see.

40:34.900 --> 40:36.083
See what?

40:36.100 --> 40:37.454
[sighs]

40:37.460 --> 40:38.450
A different man.

40:38.470 --> 40:39.892
And what's gonna
happen then?

40:39.900 --> 40:41.265
I don't know.
We're not there yet,

40:41.270 --> 40:42.590
But anything
could happen.

40:42.600 --> 40:45.137
Change brings change.

40:45.140 --> 40:49.236
You're right. I haven't
been a good father,

40:49.240 --> 40:52.733
But maybe one day,
I-I can be.

40:52.750 --> 40:53.945
You won't have
a sitter,

40:53.950 --> 40:55.270
And trent
will be working,

40:55.280 --> 40:57.271
And you'll need someone
to take care of ethan.

40:57.280 --> 40:58.816
Maybe you'll pick up
the phone and call me,

40:58.820 --> 41:04.156
And I can--I can take
him to eat or a movie.

41:06.190 --> 41:10.559
That's not gonna
happen, jack.

41:10.560 --> 41:12.392
Ok.

41:14.130 --> 41:16.667
Let me stay anyway.

41:18.500 --> 41:21.333
I got nowhere else
to go.

41:23.240 --> 41:25.834
I don't know, jack.

41:29.680 --> 41:31.978
My minute's up.

41:31.990 --> 41:34.789
You listened. That's all
I could hope for.

41:34.790 --> 41:38.158
[music playing]
